# No trailing slash: `node_modules/` matches only a directory, so a worktree's
# `node_modules` SYMLINK (agents `ln -s <main>/node_modules` to run builds/tests)
# slipped past it — showing as `?? node_modules`, getting staged by `git add -A`,
# and failing `npm run close`'s clean-tree gate. Bare `node_modules` ignores the
# symlink too (#1111).
node_modules
test/a1test*
test/a2test*
test/*.e
demos/*.e
src/*.e
tests/fixtures/*.e
test/*.o
demos/*.o
src/*.o
*.bst
*.hex
!tests/fixtures/**/*.hex
test/*.lst
demos/*.lst
src/*.lst
tests/fixtures/*.lst
name.nnn
ex0306.a
demos/demo*1.a
demos/ptest.a
demos/ptest.o
.vscode/*
test/*.bin
# scratch/ source test files (.a/.js) are tracked; ignore only generated
# build artifacts and the per-user author file (#1483).
scratch/*.e
scratch/*.lst
scratch/*.bst
scratch/*.o
scratch/*.ep
scratch/name.nnn
plusdemos/*.ep
plusdemos_tests/*.ep
cit118demos/
lccjs.zip
.env
SECRETS.txt
coverage/
puzzles.xml
scratch.md
progress-report.md
progress-report-2.md
progress-report-3.md
docs/velocity-report.md
refactor-plan-wave-2.md
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/orchestrate.json
.claire/
# Symlink assembly point into the external hermes-config SSOT repo
# (~/Documents/hermes-config). Local-only; not part of the lccjs tree. (#1372)
hermes-skills/
stats/puzzle-velocity-enriched.csv

# Playwright output
test-results/
playwright-report/

# Generated showcase/playground site (#1075).
# docs/site/** is rebuilt from source by `npm run build:site`, and CI (the Pages
# workflow) is the sole producer of what actually deploys. Committing it only
# created churn + merge conflicts and dirtied the tree on every local build,
# blocking `npm run close`. The hand-maintained CDN language support it COPIES
# from (src/lang-lcc/lang-lcc.cdn.js, #1176) is tracked; the webpack bundle it
# copies is built on demand, not committed (see below).
docs/site/

# Webpack browser bundles (#1178) — generated by `npm run build:browser`, and
# rebuilt fresh by CI on every Pages deploy (.github/workflows/pages.yml).
# They transitively bundle src/core/** + src/utils/**, so committing them
# chronically staled the tree on nearly every toolchain commit. build:site /
# serve:site now build them on demand if missing. File-specific (not `dist/`
# wholesale) so any future hand-maintained dist/ file stays tracked; includes
# the Terser-emitted .LICENSE.txt companions.
dist/lcc.bundle.js
dist/lcc.bundle.js.LICENSE.txt
dist/lcc-injector.js
dist/lcc-injector.js.LICENSE.txt
dist/editor.bundle.js
dist/editor.bundle.js.LICENSE.txt
